temporarily disable auto-insert-mode when creating HTML files

commit.message:
temporarily disable auto-insert-mode when creating HTML files

auto-insert-mode is a minor mode which automatically inserts text
whenever find-file creates a new file.  It's used for license
statements and boilerplate "skeleton code".

In the case of HTML files, it will prompt the user for a webpage
title then write in a skeleton HTML file.  This interferes with
org-static-blog.

The solution is to temporarily set auto-insert to nil when opening
a new file.  This tells auto-insert-mode to stay out of our way.

commit.message:
Fix org-static-blog-get-body logic

As far as I understood, the logic should find where the postamble div is, assuming it is immediately after content div, then skip the comments div if any.

The fix is to correct this logic, without it when comments are enabled, it will make the index page look wrong when `org-static-blog-use-preview nil`.
